#compdef presenterm-export
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# mfontanini/presenterm-export pyproject.toml `[project.scripts]
# presenterm-export = "presenterm_export.cli:main"` entry point
# + presenterm_export/cli.py argparse `parser.add_argument(...)`
# calls. Only 2 flags + a REMAINDER positional for the wrapped
# program arguments.
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
# mfontanini presenterm-export R137c — companion tool to the
# `presenterm` terminal-based presentation tool (already covered
# in the corpus). Captures the terminal output of a presenterm
# session and exports it to PDF. Uses libtmux to drive a tmux
# session for the capture.

_arguments -s -S \
  '--emit-intermediate[emit intermediate files for testing/debugging]' \
  '--version[print version and exit]' \
  '*:presenterm command + arguments (after --):_command_names -e'
